lose devices, finding the device in the list, start pairing process all over again, although I did it yesterday for example. If you didn’t address all parts of the previous question, ask them now. Short questions only. One question at a time is mandatory!\nAnswer: I see. To clarify, is it the inconvenience of having to repeatedly pair the device with your Bluetooth, even after you have already done so in the past, that makes it a frustrating experience for you?\n\n\n--- Conversation 5 ---\nQuestion: yes. exactly. If you didn’t address all parts of the previous question, ask them now. Short questions only. One question at a time is mandatory!\nAnswer: Thank you for the confirmation. Overall, how does the experience of using the product affect your willingness to recommend it to a friend? [/INST]', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=0, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=100, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None, extra_args=None), prompt_token_ids: None, prompt_embeds shape: None, lora_request: None, prompt_adapter_request: None.
